docs.lead_paragraph: SANIBEL ISLAND, Fla. -- Some years ago Sanibel's sea shells inspired Anne Morrow Lindbergh to write the best-seller "Gift From the Sea." Admittedly, shelling does not turn everybody into a philosopher or a writer, but if you spend any time at all here, you've almost got to become some kind of conchologist.
